This paper discusses the security risks associated with third-party content inclusions in websites, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the difficulty in detecting and blocking malicious third-party content, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE) and network security (cs.NI). The use of cloaking techniques in malware is also mentioned, which could be related to system and information security (cs.SI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
